tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE sensitive_access_logs (
  log_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  access_timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  accessed_table VARCHAR(50),
  query TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE sensitive_data (
  data_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
  data_name VARCHAR(50),
  data_type VARCHAR(50),
  data_value TEXT,
  access_count INT
);

CREATE TABLE sensitive_data_access_log (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  accessed_data TEXT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE user_credentials (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username TEXT,
  password TEXT,
  last_login TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE access_permissions (
  access_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  data_type TEXT,
  access_level INT
)

CREATE TABLE access_logs (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    accessed_data VARCHAR(255),
    access_time TIMESTAMP,
    access_type VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE access_tracking (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    accessed_table VARCHAR(50),
    access_time TIMESTAMP,
    access_result VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE AccessLogs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    access_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL,
    accessed_data TEXT NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE Users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    password VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE DataSources (
    source_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    source_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    source_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE AccessHistory (
    history_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT NOT NULL,
    accessed_data TEXT NOT NULL,
    access_time TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE UserRoles (
    role_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    role_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL
)
